race.comment: MAGURTZ (6) two-start Maiden who finds a weaker contest after fading late when fifth over 1200m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Tackles a more suitable contest and expected to go close from the low gate. BELLARATA (4) four-year-old mare by Pierata from Bellevue Girl on debut for the Waterhouse & Bott stable. Has trialled on seven occasions leading into today's race and can figure prominently in this winnable race. LA POTENZA (8) resumes from a lengthy break without a trial after showing potential in her first campaign. Stalked the speed when a battling second over 1015m at Grafton. Expected to have strengthened over the spell and worth thought. VILLAINESS (14) has looked plain in her two career starts and drops back a level for this. Covered ground from the gate and never looked a chance when eighth over 1200m at Gosford in a Super Mdn. Looking for a top-four finish at this level.
